Belka Says Zloty Departs from Polish Fundamentals, Hurts Inflation Fight

-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 
2011-09-22T12:06:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/belka-says-zloty-departs-from-polish-fundamentals-hurts-inflation-fight.html
The zloty exchange rate “is
becoming removed from the healthy fundamentals” of the Polish
economy and is making it harder for policy makers to control
inflation, central bank Governor Marek Belka was quoted today as
saying in an interview with the bank’s Obserwatorfinansowy.pl
website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David McQuaid at 
 dmcquaid1@bloomberg.net  